  "texts": [
    "As a summary, the parity-odd tripsectrum from massive scalar exchange is thus finite and scale-invariant and can be exactly computed to beB ζ,PO 4 = i π 5 ∆ 4 ζ 32 ρ H H Λ 6 Γ 11 2 -ν Γ 11 2 +ν (k 1 •k 2) [k 1 •(k 2 ×k 3)] k 1 k 3 2 k 3 3 k 7 4 × 1-k 2 ∂ ∂k 2 1-k 3 ∂ ∂k 3 2 F1 11 2 -ν, 11 2 +ν 6 1 2 - k 123 2k 4 +23 perms.",
    "(5.72)We point out that this example is, to our knowledge, the first one realising a tree-level parity-violating trispectrum in a pure scalar theory.",
    "Its analytic structure is also distinct from other examples involving triple vertices.",
    "Notably, there is only a single hypergeometric function of kinematics.",
    "This simplification arises from the fact that linear coupling reduces the other hypergeometric function to a constant."
